Personally I don't think the shotgun is as OP as people complain it is. I think most of the time it just seems that way if you have inferior ping. The shotgun SHOULD do enormous damage if you fire it at point blank range. When players all have good ping it is a lot more difficult to get close enough to fire off the shotgun at that range. Reducing the range is probably a good idea but in matches where the opponent and I both have good ping I've never found the shotgun to be too powerful when using it or playing against it.

The knife complaints are a similar issue in my opinion. I'd say the range is a little longer than it should be and the stun should really only happen if you are at point blank range but the damage is probably ok. Once again, when bad ping is taken out of the equation the knife isn't OP at all. 

The ping issue, even when it's equally bad for all players, is what is making most of the weapons unusable. You can't use most of the longer range weapons because the aim assist always has you firing at places which might look correct but are no longer where the opponent is because of the ping. Because of this the close up weapons seem more powerful than they are because most of the time you have to get right up next to an opponent to actually deal damage and then of course the ones that have benefits for being close up (shotgun and knife) are going to shine. The rocket launcher is the only long range weapon that is useful and the main reason for that is because you can hang back and let the other players get right next to each other (which they have to because of the ping) and then fire off a rocket and either kill the last one standing or get multiple kills at once. 

Once the ping issues are fixed (everyone having equally bad ping is not fixed!) you will actually get to see how each weapon plays out. Tinkering with power levels before that time is just a way to change up which weapon will be complained about as being OP until the next change has to happen.
